English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>tūn</i>. The Northamptonshire derives from an Old English personal name <i>Hǣthhere</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. Compare   Herendeen  .","Irish: adopted as an Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hArrachtáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Arrachtán</i>’, a personal name from a diminutive of <i>arrachtach</i> ‘mighty, powerful’.","Irish: in Kerry, this name was adopted as an Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hIongardail</b>, later <b>Ó hUrdáil</b>, ‘descendant of <i>Iongardal</i>’, a personal name of uncertain origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Herington","meanings":["English: variant of   Harrington   or   Herrington  ."]},{"name":"Herrington","meanings":["English:","habitational name from Heronden in Tenterden (Kent) or Herrington in Houghton (Durham). The Kent placename may derive from an Old English personal name <i>Hȳra</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>denn</i> ‘pasture’, while the Durham placename may come from Old English <i>hæring</i> ‘rocky place’ (from <i>hær</i> ‘rock, heap of stones’ + the placename forming suffix <i>-ing</i>) or <i>hæren</i> ‘rocky’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’.","variant of   Harrington  ."]},{"name":"Herendeen","meanings":["Altered form of English   Harrington  ."]},{"name":"Arrington","meanings":["English:","variant of   Harrington   with loss of initial <i>H-</i>.","possibly a habitational name from Arrington, a place in Cambridgeshire, named from an Old English byname, <i>Earn(a)</i>, meaning ‘eagle’ + <i>-inga-</i> ‘people or followers of’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘settlement’."]}]},{"name":"Lady","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>lavedi</i>, <i>levedi</i>, <i>ladi</i> ‘lady, female head of a household, woman, wife’ (Old English <i>hlǣfdige</i>). As a man's name it may have been used in mockery, or be short for occupational names such as <b>Ladyman</b>.","Polish: variant of   Lada  .","Hungarian (<b>Ládi</b>): habitational name for someone from Lád in Borsod County or Lad in Somogy County."],"variants":[{"name":"Lada","meanings":["‘tendril’ or ‘creeper’, often used in metaphors describing the slender curvature of eyebrows, arms, hair, swords, lightning, and women's bodies."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."],"variants":[{"name":"Anni","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Anne Harrington was born in 1505, in Westmorland, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Sir John Edward Bart Harrington High Sheriff of Rutland. She married Lancelot Plantagenet  Lancaster in 1520, in Westmorland, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died after 1531, in her hometown."},"et":{"1505–After 1531":"1505–pärast 1531","1505–1531":"1505–1531","1500–1607":"1500–1607","–1574":"–1574","0070–1524":"0070–1524","1524":"1524","1500":"1500","1520":"1520","1531":"1531","1574":"1574","5 Nov 1524":"5. november 1524","1607":"1607","After 1531":"pärast 1531","1505":"1505","0070":"0070","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ubery Hall, Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Exton, Devon, England":"Exton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1505–After 1531":"1505–1531 jälkeen","1505–1531":"1505–1531","1500–1607":"1500–1607","–1574":"–1574","0070–1524":"0070–1524","1524":"1524","1500":"1500","1520":"1520","1531":"1531","1574":"1574","5 Nov 1524":"5. marraskuuta 1524","1607":"1607","After 1531":"1531 jälkeen","1505":"1505","0070":"0070","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ubery Hall, Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Exton, Devon, England":"Exton, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1505–After 1531":